               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210606-112-person1261">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JAMES SALMON
               <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1261" type="surname" value="JAMES SALMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1261" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am patrol of Bow-street. On the 20th of April, about nine o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner at Paddington, and followed him into a pawnbroker's, and saw him offer to pawn a table-spoon for 15 s. - Mr. Ross would not take it in; he said his master, Mr. Gibbons of Marylebone-lane, sent him to pawn it. I followed him out and took him into custody; I asked what he had about him, he denied having anything. I found the spoon in his coat; he then said, he took it from 
               <persName id="t18210606-112-person1262">
                  Baron 
                  De Montesquieu
               <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1262" type="surname" value="De Montesquieu"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1262" type="given" value="Baron"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's, and took me to the house in <placeName id="t18210606-112-crimeloc652">Upper Seymour-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210606-112-crimeloc652" type="placeName" value="Upper Seymour-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210606-112-crimeloc652" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210606-112-off649 t18210606-112-crimeloc652"></join> - the servant claimed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210606-112-person1263">
                  JOSEPH 
                  GIBBONS
               <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1263" type="surname" value="GIBBONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1263" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1263" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter; the prisoner was my <rs id="t18210606-112-deflabel653" type="occupation">apprentice</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210606-112-defend1257 t18210606-112-deflabel653"></join>; my house was burnt down, and the Baron gave me leave to be in his; the prisoner came there occasionally, but did not sleep there. I did not send him to pawn the spoon - he has been four years with me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210606-112-person1264">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SHILLETON
               <interp inst="t18210606-112-person1264" type="surname" value="SHILLETON"></interp>
